<br>
The root cause of this problem is that there was never a clear role for the hybrid tanks.  Thiey used to tank less well, and do less damage, but had spells to make up for that.  The spells however didn't make up anything in a group situation.  They provided a nice bonus to soloing power, but nothing to the group.  Then the Shadowknights and Paladins had their melee skills beefed up and got more individual spells that were desireable while grouping.  <br>
<br>
The core problem still remains, there are three flavors of tank and you only need one.  The one you need is the one that can hold the monster.  I almost never use defensive, as I would rather the monster hit me while non-defensive than hit the rogue or the druid or the wizard, etc.  I would gladly have my damage reduced to half for a x4 aggro modifier (net gain of double aggro), as my dps is laughably insignificant to my usual group (Me: 60-80 dps, Rogue: 105-130 dps, DC pet: 100-110 dps, Chanter: ~20 dps, Cleric ~20 dps, Wizard: alot :P). <br>
<br>
Bottom line:  All tanks must be able to direct the monster's attention at themselves.  Good tanks must be able handle the punishment the mob puts out.  I hold aggro pretty well in my normal group, as they know my limits, but have been passed over for knights or put in a non-tanking position by pickup groups.  <br>
<br>
I see no reason why knights should taunt better than warriors now.  We do similar damage, and tank pretty much the same on xp mobs.  We do have a decided advantage on raid mobs, but I personally use that as little as possible (my guild is small and more accustomed to group aggro than raid aggro).  Knights are better at soloing and duoing than warriors due to their spells.  I think ALL tanks should be allowed to demand aggro, use damage taken, damage delt, and utility as balancing factors.<br>
<br>
Changes I would like to see made to the warrior class:<br>
<br>
1) Improve Aggro Production:  Put us on equal footing with knights for aggro production, both instant, and long term.  Remove Enraging Blow and it's cousins from the game.<br>
<br>
2) Permanent Mitigation Bonus:  Give us a permanent mitigation bonus of 20% (maxhit = DB + 16 DI) so that we never get hit as hard as another class.  In return take defensive away, or hell all the disciplines as far as I care.  <br>
<br>
3) Soloability:  Yeah I know, it isn't a solo game.  Most classes have a much greater proficiency at it however, and we should be able to make some xp on our own when we dont have time to commit to a group.  We need to improve our soloability without increasing group effectiveness.  Do this by making us virtually immune to damage from green and light blue mobs.  This will allow us to chain kill light blue mobs for a steady stream of low grade xp.  It isn't glorious, but would be a great fit for those times when you have half an hour to play.<br>
<br>
Wow, I gotta stop going afk while I am posting ... I have rambled on a bit too long.<br>
<br>
