<br>
From a shaman's perspective, I much prefer to have a mob malo'd by the time it gets to camp and slow it immediately. A good SK will never loose agro, a warrior will. Not that taking a hit or two is a big deal, I'm much prefer to have a slowed mob beating on me for a few seconds than an unslowed mob on the MT but it does show the agro differences and with a warrior it can get hairy with a resisted slow and a missed taunt right after. <br>
<br>
**hugs shield and warriors that know how to use it** <br>
<br>
Especially in a non-ideal group (druid/shaman healing for example) were the margin of error isn't that big, having a warrior for MT is a pretty major disadvantage. Honestly though, I sometimes get the feeling that it's often due to warriors that don't know when to hit the taunt button. Some warriors just seem to taunt well while others don't and from what I've seen it doesn't seem to be gear dependent. <br>
<br>
Having said that, the only reason I'm reading this board atm is because I'm gearing up a warrior alt, not a knight, but taunt really is broken at the high end. At least the difference in taunt between warrior and knights, I guess you could debate whether knights taunt too well or warriors don't taunt well enough.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bergum>Bergum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/03 1:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2815.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Shaman here,<br>
